    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><style>[data-colorid=vsyvhk10yp]{color:#808284} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=vsyvhk10yp]{color:#7b7d7f}</style><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" width=\"793\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544647320/RenderMan_Solaris_Lighting.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433165324&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=793&amp;height=429\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544647320/RenderMan_Solaris_Lighting.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433165324&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"693\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544647336\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Solaris_Lighting.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544647320\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"5\" data-media-id=\"03fddfc6-ca6b-42ee-832e-0e69f4e4071e\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544647320/RenderMan_Solaris_Lighting.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433165324&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1586&amp;height=858 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544647320/RenderMan_Solaris_Lighting.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433165324&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=793&amp;height=429 1x\" /></span><h3 id=\"RenderManforHoudiniReleaseNotes-WelcometoRenderManforHoudini\">Welcome to RenderMan for Houdini</h3><p>RenderMan for Houdini (RfH) continues to provide full support for the latest RenderMan.&nbsp; See the <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://rmanwiki-27.pixar.com/space/REN27/542238759/\" rel=\"nofollow\">RenderMan Release Notes</a> for more details.</p><p>This current release offers support for:</p><ul><li><p>Houdini 21.0</p></li><li><p>Houdini 20.5</p></li><li><p>Houdini 20.0</p></li></ul><p>Please see the release notes below for all the new capabilities and known issues.&nbsp; See the <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFH27/pages/544640398/Installation+of+RenderMan+for+Houdini\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544640398\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Installation of RenderMan for Houdini</a> page for the list of specific production builds RfH works with.</p><p /><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-information conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"5ef14c8e-076b-4081-82f9-5271e16fedd5\" data-macro-name=\"info\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>Rendering with RenderMan will not operate on Houdini Apprentice editions. See SideFX's website for options that allow Third Party Rendering</p></div></div><h3 id=\"RenderManforHoudiniReleaseNotes-KnownLimitations\">Known Limitations<br /></h3><h4 id=\"RenderManforHoudiniReleaseNotes-Solaris\">Solaris</h4><ul><li><p>Due to a SideFx limitation, there are some shading network circumstances where the visualizer node doesn't solo networks correctly</p></li></ul><h4 id=\"RenderManforHoudiniReleaseNotes-MaterialXLama\">MaterialX Lama</h4><ul><li><p>Soloing complex MaterialX Lama shading networks.</p></li></ul><h4 id=\"RenderManforHoudiniReleaseNotes-XPU\">XPU</h4><ul><li><p>CUDA device is saved in the scene rather than as a preference.</p></li></ul><h4 id=\"RenderManforHoudiniReleaseNotes-General\">General</h4><ul><li><p>Rendering to IT with ACES currently needs the env variable <strong>IT_OCIOV1 </strong>to be set to your ACES config.ocio</p></li><li><p>Render with Takes is not supported.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>Rendering with Mantra lights or VOPs is not possible</p></li><li><p>Bypassing shader nodes</p></li><li><p>Auto camera creation for IPR</p></li><li><p>RenderMan clipping planes</p></li><li><p>Display edits cannot changed from the image tool to mplay</p></li><li><p>Cross-frame denoising PDG support.</p></li><li><p>Applying undo of deleted nodes or collapsing to subnet may not work as expected</p></li><li><p>Rewiring subnet indirect inputs<br /><br /></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"300\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544647320/inside-out-2-sadness-01.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433165324&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=300&amp;height=417\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544647320/inside-out-2-sadness-01.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433165324&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"1024\" data-width=\"735\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544647339\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"inside-out-2-sadness-01.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544647320\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"5\" data-media-id=\"4e7c304a-3255-4171-843a-55917a76e1c9\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544647320/inside-out-2-sadness-01.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433165324&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=600&amp;height=834 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544647320/inside-out-2-sadness-01.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433165324&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=300&amp;height=417 1x\" /></span><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span data-colorid=\"vsyvhk10yp\">Inside Out 2 &copy; Disney/Pixar</span></p>"
    }
